Makes: 1 loafDifficulty: EasyIngredients: cup peanut butter1/3 cup butter2 eggs cup sugar4 ripe medium sized bananas, mashed250g bacon, chopped and fried until crispy (reserve the fat after frying) tsp vanilla extract2 cups flour2 tsp baking powder tsp saltNot just for toast: 11 peanut butter recipes you'll go nuts for Method:1) Preheat the oven to 180 C. Line a 2L loaf pan with baking paper.2) Melt the butter and peanut butter together.3) Beat the eggs and sugar until pale and thick.4) Add the melted peanut butter and butter and beat until combined. 5) Mix in the bananas, bacon and vanilla extract.6) Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together in a separate bowl. 7) Add the flour mixture to the egg mixture and mix until just combined.8) Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan and smooth the top.7) Bake for 50-60 minutes; the bread will be ready when a toothpick inserted into the middle comes out clean. Let the bread cool for a bit in the pan, then turn out onto a wire rack, remove the baking paper and allow to cool completely.